 \int_0^a f(a - x) \; \mathrm d x = \int f(0) \; \mathrm dx - \int f(a)  \;\mathrm dx = \int_a^0 f(x) \; \mathrm dx 
f(a - x) = f(a) - f(x)
 \begin{align*} \int_0^a f(a - x) d x &= - \int_a^0 f(y) d y \qquad \text{by \(y = a - x\), \(d y = - dx\)} \\                       &= \int_0^a f(y) d y   \qquad \text{turn around limits} \end{align*} 
